The paper deals with the problem of ranking and measuring the significance of variable-length motifs in time series data. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), data mining (cs.DM), information retrieval (cs.IR), signal processing (cs.SI), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, given the focus on similarity-based motifs and dissimilarity measures, we believe cs.LG and cs.DM are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IR, cs.SI, and cs.AI.
